meconic.d:
a. Pertaining to, or obtained from, the poppy or opium;
   specif. (Chem.), designating an acid related to aconitic acid, found in
   opium and extracted as a white crystalline substance.

meiny.d:
n. A family, including servants, etc.; household; retinue;
   train.
n. Company; band; army.

mephistophelian.d:
a. Pertaining to, or resembling, the devil
   Mephistopheles, "a crafty, scoffing, relentless fiend;" devilish;
   crafty.
